My advice to you would be to give up. You can’t code a server with as much knowledge as you portray. But if you wish to prove me wrong I will define what I mean.
Renamed means you have files like itemDef.java instead of Class8.java in your CLIENT. Preloading (never really got into it) means you load your models through your cache and now through a folder named “models”. Remember this is all CLIENT sided. Now can you tell me which you have?
